<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Canada:  draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>2006/&#8230;  Human rights and mass exoduses 
</b></p>
<p> <i>The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p> <i>Recalling</i> Commission on Human Rights resolution 2005/48 of 19 April 2005, 
</p>
<p> <i>Calls upon</i> States, intergovernmental bodies and concerned international organizations to 
continue to respond to the assistance and protection needs of forcibly displaced populations, to 
intensify their cooperation to address human rights situations that can lead to mass exoduses, to 
promote comprehensive approaches involving all relevant stakeholders, to identify durable 
solutions for refugees and internally displaced persons and to prevent new flows of refugees and 
internally displaced persons from becoming protracted. 
</p>
